## Testing

### Unit Tests

```typescript
describe("OAuth callback", () => {
  it("rejects requests without code parameter", async () => {
    const req = new NextRequest("http://localhost/api/auth/github/callback");
    const res = await GET(req);
    expect(res.status).toBe(400);
  });

  it("rejects requests with invalid state", async () => {
    // Set a state cookie, then send request with different state
    const req = new NextRequest(
      "http://localhost/api/auth/github/callback?code=abc&state=wrong",
    );
    const res = await GET(req);
    expect(res.status).toBe(403);
  });

  it("rejects non-owner GitHub users", async () => {
    // Mock GitHub API to return user with different ID
    // Set ALLOWED_GITHUB_USER_ID to a different value
    const res = await GET(validRequest);
    expect(res.status).toBe(403);
  });

  it("creates session and redirects for valid owner", async () => {
    // Mock GitHub API to return correct user
    // Set ALLOWED_GITHUB_USER_ID to match
    const res = await GET(validRequest);
    expect(res.status).toBe(307); // redirect
    expect(res.headers.get("set-cookie")).toContain("gblockparty-session");
  });
});
```

### Manual Verification

1. Start the dashboard dev server: `pnpm dev:dashboard`
2. Open `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/github` in a browser
3. Authorize the app on GitHub
4. Verify redirect back to `http://localhost:3000`
5. Check browser cookies for `gblockparty-session`
6. Visit `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me` and verify user data is returned
